FBIS4-8189 "dreeu070_i_94018" FBIS-EEU-94-070 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA UNPROFOR Spokesman on Request for Air Strikes UNPROFOR Spokesman on Request for Air Strikes LD1104184594 Paris TF-1 Television Network in French 1800 GMT 11 Apr 94 LD1104184594 Paris TF-1 Television Network French BFN [Excerpts] There has been another raid by U.S. aircraft on the Serb positions that have been besieging the Muslim town of Gorazde. [passage omitted] Naida Nakad reports: [Nakad] [passage omitted] The commander of UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] in Bosnia called for this intervention. The UN spokesman in Sarajevo explains: [Begin E. Chaperon recording] The situation remained calm during the night and this morning, unfortunately, the Serbs resumed their advance, they resumed their thrust toward the town, and they jeopardized the safety of our staff once again. This is what led General Rose to call for the agreement to air strikes. This took place at 1407. The planes launched the attack at 1419. [end recording] [passage omitted]
